SEARCH
Package org.bluezoo.gumdrop.ldap.client

Interface SearchResultHandler

public interface SearchResultHandler
Handler for search operation results.

Search results are delivered incrementally. This handler receives:

  1. Zero or more handleEntry(org.bluezoo.gumdrop.ldap.client.SearchResultEntry) calls for matching entries
  2. Zero or more handleReference(java.lang.String[]) calls for referrals
  3. Exactly one handleDone(org.bluezoo.gumdrop.ldap.client.LDAPResult, org.bluezoo.gumdrop.ldap.client.LDAPSession) call when the search completes

The order of entries and references depends on the server implementation and may be interleaved.

Author:
Chris Burdess
See Also:

  • Method Details

    • handleEntry

      void handleEntry(SearchResultEntry entry)
      Called for each matching entry.

      This method may be called zero or more times, once for each entry that matches the search criteria.

      Parameters:
      entry - the search result entry

    • handleReference

      void handleReference(String[] referralUrls)
      Called for each search result reference (referral).

      Referrals indicate that part of the search results may be available from other servers. The handler can choose to follow referrals by opening new connections to the referenced servers.

      Parameters:
      referralUrls - LDAP URLs pointing to other servers

    • handleDone

      void handleDone(LDAPResult result, LDAPSession session)
      Called when the search operation completes.

      This is always called exactly once, after all entries and references have been delivered. The result indicates the overall status of the search.

      Common result codes:

      • SUCCESS - search completed normally
      • SIZE_LIMIT_EXCEEDED - more entries exist but limit reached
      • TIME_LIMIT_EXCEEDED - search took too long
      • NO_SUCH_OBJECT - base DN does not exist
      Parameters:
      result - the search result status
      session - operations for further directory access
